text: Abraham Jamal Hamadeh (born May 15, 1991) is an American politician, former prosecutor, and U.S. Army intelligence officer. He is the member of the U.S. House of Representatives for since 2025. Hamadeh was the Republican Party nominee for Arizona Attorney General in the 2022 election, losing the election by 280 votes. ==References== ==Other websites== * Official campaign website * Biography at Ballotpedia * * Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:Politicians from Chicago Category:Lawyers from Chicago Category:Politicians from Phoenix, Arizona Category:Lawyers from Phoenix, Arizona Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians Category:United States representatives from Arizona
